        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Starter Scaffold Templates and Repo Structure"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A starter scaffold template is a pre-built repository skeleton that engineers instantiate when beginning a new Claude integration. The scaffold is not a blank directory with a README — it is a fully wired project that can run its CI gate pipeline, pass all fitness function checks, and register itself in the IDP service catalog on day one. The value of a scaffold is not convenience; it is correctness. Without one, engineers make different structural choices for each integration — some put prompts in src/, some inline them in handler code, some omit eval suites entirely. With a scaffold, all integrations have the same layout, the same tooling entry points, and the same CI gates from the start."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Diagram: Claude feature scaffold repository structure — annotated directory tree with prompts, src, evals, tests, CI, docs, and catalog files",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What the Scaffold Provides"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The scaffold pre-wires every component of the paved road so that engineers start from a known-good baseline rather than assembling the pieces themselves:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prompt template directory: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "the prompts/ directory with a seed YAML template that has all required fields filled in with placeholders — model_id, max_tokens, safety_baseline_version, capability_list, and token budget fields. Engineers replace the placeholders with their integration's actual values."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Application source files: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "handler.py (or handler.ts), context_builder.py, and response_parser.py — the three standard modules of a Claude integration. Each file has the correct imports, a function signature that matches the client library's expected usage, and structured logging calls in the right places."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Seed eval suite: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "10 eval cases in golden_dataset.jsonl — five examples of correct DO behaviour and five examples of DO NOT behaviour that should be refused. These are placeholder cases that engineers replace with real cases for their integration, but having 10 cases on day one ensures CI eval gate has something to run."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Pre-wired CI pipeline: ",
