      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Updating Scaffolds Without Breaking Existing Integrations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The scaffold versioning problem"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Once a team instantiates a scaffold, the files are copied into their repository. Subsequent updates to the scaffold template do not automatically propagate to existing integrations. This creates a versioning problem: over time, integrations drift away from the current scaffold conventions. The mitigation strategies:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Scaffold version annotation in catalog-info.yaml: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "every catalog entry records the scaffold version used to create it. The IDP shows a warning badge when the integration is more than one major scaffold version behind."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Scaffold migration guide on major version bumps: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "when the scaffold has a major version bump (e.g., changing the CI workflow structure), the platform team publishes a migration guide in the IDP that lists the specific files to update."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Architecture drift detection for CI workflow structure: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "the architecture.json baseline includes the expected CI workflow jobs. If an integration's workflow drifts from the required set of jobs, the drift gate flags it."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Opt-in sync tool: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "teams can run npm run scaffold:sync (or equivalent) to apply non-breaking scaffold updates to their existing integration — updating dependency versions, linting rules, and CI job names without overwriting integration-specific code."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "First Steps After Instantiating the Scaffold"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After running the scaffold via the IDP portal, the engineer has a repository with all placeholder values. The minimum set of changes before the first PR:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Replace template_id: my-feature with the integration's actual name in prompts/my-feature.yml (and rename the file)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fill in the capability_list with the real DO and DO NOT items for this integration."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Replace the 10 placeholder eval cases in evals/golden_dataset.jsonl with real input/expected-behaviour pairs."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Update src/handler.py to call the correct template_id and pass the correct context_data fields."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Set require_security_reviewer: true in prompts/my-feature.yml if this is a customer-facing integration."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Update catalog-info.yaml with the integration's real description and owner team."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Run npm run ci:gates locally to confirm all gates pass before opening the first PR."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The scaffold's placeholder eval cases will pass the eval gate on day one — because the placeholder expected behaviour is 'DO' and any response that is not a refusal satisfies it. Engineers must replace the placeholder cases with real cases before the eval gate becomes meaningful. This is the most important step after instantiating the scaffold."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Starter scaffold templates provide a fully wired repository skeleton for new Claude integrations. The scaffold pre-installs the prompt template directory, application source modules, seed eval suite, CI gate pipeline, architecture drift baseline, IDP catalog registration, and documentation templates. Engineers start from a known-good baseline rather than assembling the paved road from scratch. The scaffold has four variants (Python service, TypeScript service, Python Lambda, Python batch) that all share the same directory structure and CI pipeline skeleton. After instantiation, the engineer replaces placeholder values with integration-specific content — capability list, eval cases, handler logic — before the first PR."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The scaffold's greatest value is structural consistency: all integrations share the same layout, making it predictable where to find each type of file."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Seed eval cases are placeholders that pass CI on day one — replacing them with real cases is the most important post-instantiation step."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The CI pipeline is pre-wired but not pre-configured: engineers must set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in GitHub Secrets and provision a staging environment before Gate 2 and Gate 3 can run."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Scaffold versioning is tracked in catalog-info.yaml; integrations more than one major version behind are flagged in the IDP with a warning badge."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Architecture drift detection for CI workflow structure ensures integrations do not quietly remove required gate jobs over time."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}